!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = Cell suspensions were then washed, counted, pooled, concentrated, and subjected to 5â² single-cell RNA sequencing using the Chromium Next GEM Single Cell 5â² Kit v2 and Chromium Next GEM Chip K Single Cell Kit (10x Genomics, Pleasanton, CA, USA), targeting a recovery of 10,000 cells using manufacturerâs protocols. Sequencing libraries were prepared using the Library Construction Kit (10x Genomics, Pleasanton, CA, USA) and sequenced on an Illumina NextSeq 2000. Cells were stained using TotalSeq-C hashtag and CITE-Seq antibodies. Cell suspensions were then washed, counted, pooled, concentrated, and subjected to 5â² single-cell RNA sequencing using the Chromium Next GEM Single Cell 5â² Kit v2 and Chromium Next GEM Chip K Single Cell Kit, targeting a recovery of 10,000 cells.
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = Sequencing libraries were prepared using the 10X Genomics Library Construction Kit and sequenced on an Illumina NextSeq 2000.
!Sample_description = Library name: Patient 7, LN
!Sample_description = Multiplexed CITE-seq data from Patient7, lymph node
!Sample_data_processing = Transcriptomic reads were aligned to the GRCh38-1.2.0 reference genome and quantified using 10X CellRanger.
!Sample_data_processing = CITE-seq ADT and HTO reads were examined for antibody-oligonucleotide conjugate specific sequence barcodes through CellRangerâs feature indexing function.
!Sample_data_processing = Demultiplexing of HTO-multiplexed samples was achieved through the Seurat HTODemux algorithm.
!Sample_data_processing = Cells with high mitochondrial gene expression (>15% of entire gene expression counts), displaying a high level of ambient RNA contamination (> 0.9), or expressing less than 50 antibodies out of the 128-antibody panel were discarded prior to analysis.
!Sample_data_processing = Assembly: hg19
!Sample_data_processing = Supplementary files format and content: counts
!Sample_data_processing = Library strategy: CITE-seq
